# FreeBASIC rules — {{PROJECT}}

FreeBASIC is **not** VB.NET, VBA, QBASIC, or C — do not assume their syntax.

## Language
- Variables: `Dim As Integer x` / `Var x = 1`; strings are `String` (ASCII), `WString`/`ZString` wide/C.
- Procedures: `Sub`/`Function … End`; declare in `.bi` headers; `#include once "file.bi"`.
- Types: `Type … End Type`, `Extends`, `Declare Virtual`. Manual memory for pointers (`New`/`Delete`).
- Comments `'` or `/' … '/`; line continuation trailing `_`; identifiers case-insensitive.
- `Dim` is **procedure-scoped**, not block-scoped — a `Dim` inside an `If`/loop lives until `End Sub`.
- `IIf(...)` cannot return a `String` — use explicit `If/Else` assignment.

## Astoria project
- `{{PROJECT}}.vfp` is the manifest: every source file is a `File=` line, the main file is starred (`*File=`). Mirror any add/rename/delete there; a file not listed is invisible to the project.
- Leave the IDE-maintained `.vfp` metadata keys alone (`Author=` … `AITool=`) — the IDE round-trips them on save.
- `.frm` files are Form-Designer-managed: edit event-handler bodies freely; prefer the Designer for layout; if hand-editing, keep the `With`-block shape and `' <ControlName>` comment lines.
- GUI projects use the bundled MFF framework: `#include once "mff/<Control>.bi"`, `Using My.Sys.Forms`.
- Do not edit `Temp/`, produced `.exe` files, or `{{PROJECT}}_Change.log`.

## Build / verify
- Preferred: open the `.vfp` in the Astoria IDE, press **F5** (handles `.frm` mains, `.rc` generation, include paths).
- CLI (console): `fbc -s console <MainFile>.bas`. CLI (GUI): add `-i <AstoriaDir>\Controls\Framework`; `fbc` rejects `.frm` as direct input and the `#cmdline "<name>.rc"` needs the IDE-generated resource — prefer the IDE.
- Errors are `file(line) error N: message` — fix the FIRST error first; keep changes small and compile-checked.
